Problem 7.4

  1. group_by (“First”) refers to “First” that is not previously defined. Instead of grouping the table by “First”, the statement simply creates another column in the table and gives all rows the statement “First”. It should be name.

  2. There is an error in Summarise (Tmp, totalBirths = sum(count)). The Tmp is not needed in this case. It should only just be Summarise(totalBirths = sum(count)).

  3. There is no chaining syntax here so the previous expression of Tmp <- group_by does not get passed through to the next summarise function. This causes the program to execute the two statements separately. We need a %>% after the group_by(BabyNames, year, sex) to create a table called Tmp. Also, another error is that there is no need to explicitly say the data name BabyNames in summarise(BabyNames) when we have already called the data table before.
